Warwick Summer School Application Portal

A full-stack web application built using Flask to simulate a university summer school application system. The platform allows prospective students to browse courses and submit applications, while administrators can manage and review submissions through a secure dashboard.

---

Features

Student Side
- Browse available summer school courses
- Submit application form
- Receive confirmation page after submission

Admin Side
- Secure login system (session-based authentication)
- View all submitted applications
- Accept or reject applications
- Delete applications
- View individual application details

---

Tech Stack

- Python
- Flask
- SQLite
- HTML / CSS
- Jinja2 Templating
- Bootstrap (for responsive UI)

---

Project Structure

app.py Main Flask application
templates/ HTML templates (Jinja2)
static/ CSS, images, assets
requirements.txt Python dependencies

---

How to Run Locally

1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/41y554/warwick-flask-app.git

2. Navigate into the project
cd warwick-flask-app

3. Create virtual environment
python -m venv .venv

4. Activate virtual environment

Windows:
.venv\Scripts\activate

Then open:

http://127.0.0.1:5000/

